<title>PORTUGAL: PT labour force could grow - minister.</title>
<headline>PT labour force could grow - minister.</headline>
<dateline>LISBON 1996-11-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Portugal Telecom's labour force could increase to meet competitive challenges in the market place, Planning and Public Works Minister Joao Cravinho said.</p>
<p>&quot;The competitiveness of PT does not depend on the reduction of its workforce. There could be an increase in workers,&quot; he said after a signing ceremony to grant PT's Marconi unit the concession for its external telecommunications operations.</p>
<p>&quot;The expansion of new business will permit the expansion of employment,&quot; he added.</p>
<p>PT, which was partially privatised earlier this year, has some 22,000 employees.</p>
<p>PT shares stood at 4,120 escudos, up 45, in volume of 170,743 shares at 1310 GMT.</p>
